‚ÄúVote Spartacus!‚Äù ‚Äì üá©üá™ German Spartacus League poster, 1918, showing a massive red fist pummelling a parliament full of capitalists. The Spartacus League (Spartakusbund) was a communist movement founded in Germany during the First World War by members of the Social  Democratic Party (SPD) opposed to the war, particularly Karl Liebknecht and Rosa Luxemburg. At the end of 1918 the league became the German Communist Party and fomented an uprising in January 1919 ‚Äì the Spartacist Uprising ‚Äì that was swiftly crushed. Poster via @weimar_propaganda, gr8 resource for propaganda from the Weimar Republic (plus a bit from before and after)

Spain stands out as a beacon of peace among the carnage. Under Franco Spain was officially neutral during the Second World War ‚Äì except for the Divisi√≥n Azul, or Blue Legion, of volunteers who fought on the Eastern Front, Franco largely refused to involve Spain in the war.
